will have a residence permit that lets you stay one year in china, lets you leave and enter the country as you want, and a fair ability to travel during weekends, holidays, and the occasional class-skipping stint. for more information, visit the china scholarship council [50] and china service center for scholarly exchanges [51] websites. work[edit] teaching a language, most commonly english, is a very popular source of employment for foreigners. there are english-teaching jobs all over china. the market for teachers of other languages is more limited. however most universities require all english majors to study another foreign language 